&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 – G2 Ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about working with children and their families? Do you want to join a team that values you and your development? If so come and be part of our extraordinary team, where every day is anything other than ordinary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;G2 ward area provides 24-hour acute care for up to 24 children and covers all specialties with high dependency / close observation beds. Children are admitted either electively or in an emergency. Ward staff work closely with our community children’s nurses to reduce the Children’s length of stay on the ward. The ward area provides short stay care for children undergoing elective day surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively promote opportunities for our nurses to develop, you will also have access to regular high quality supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the trust is happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome informal questions and visits, please contact on 01256 312765 for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
